# Implementation Plan: Advanced Volatility Modeling (Jump/Drift/Skew)

Update the L1 Compute layer to support non-stationary volatility modeling, specifically targeting "V-Drift" algorithms and Skew Reversal signals found in 2024-2026 research.

## Proposed Changes

### [L1 Compute Layer]

#### [MODIFY] [microstructure.py](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/shared/models/microstructure.py)
- Update [IVVelocityResult](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/shared/models/microstructure.py#210-218) to include:
    - `iv_acceleration: float`: Time-based second derivative of IV.
    - `vol_drift: float`: EWMA-based drift term.
    - `skew: float`: OTM Put IV - OTM Call IV.
    - `skew_convexity: float`: Surface curvature (second derivative vs Strike).
    - `skew_reversal_alert: bool`: Flag for local top/bottom signals.

#### [MODIFY] [iv_velocity_tracker.py](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l1_compute/trackers/iv_velocity_tracker.py)
- Update [_DataPoint](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l1_compute/trackers/iv_velocity_tracker.py#19-23) to store `put_iv` and `call_iv`.
- Update [update()](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l1_compute/trackers/iv_velocity_tracker.py#43-89) to calculate `iv_acceleration` and `vol_drift`.
- Implement `skew_reversal` detection logic:
    - Trigger `BULLISH_REVERSAL` if Skew flips positive at a price bottom.
    - Trigger `BEARISH_REVERSAL` if Skew flips negative (Calls becoming more expensive than Puts) at a price top.

#### [MODIFY] [reactor.py](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l1_compute/reactor.py)
- Locate OTM Put and OTM Call options (e.g., ±5 strike offset or 25-delta) in [_compute_sync](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l1_compute/reactor.py#195-375).
- Pass these IVs to `IVVelocityTracker.update()`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- **New Unit Test**: Create `e:\US.market\Option_v3\l1_compute\trackers\tests\test_iv_velocity_advanced.py` to verify:
    - Accuracy of `iv_acceleration` calculation.
    - `vol_drift` convergence over time.
    - Skew reversal signal triggering using synthetic "Skew Flip" data.
- **Integration Test**: Run `pytest e:\US.market\Option_v3\l1_compute\tests\test_reactor.py` to ensure no regressions in the main pipeline.

